China Children's Center to hold a series of activities for children to experience "high-tech" during Children's Day - Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, May 20th (Huang Xiaoxi, Zhou Shanshan) Reporters learned from the China Children's Center on the 20th that from May 28th to June 1st, around Children's Day, the China Children's Center plans to hold a series of activities such as children's maker experience, children's visual art festival, and parent-child book carnival, allowing children to spend Children's Day immersed in the charm of cutting-edge technology. It is understood that the activities held by the China Children's Center during this year's Children's Day include "Love Home, Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival, the first Children's Visual Art Festival, "Book Fragrance Carnival" activity, "Family Loves Reading" picture book series activities, and more. Li Zhongming, deputy director of the China Children's Center, introduced at the media briefing for the 2016 Children's Day on the 20th that the "Love Home, Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival is the key activity of this year's China Children's Center to celebrate Children's Day. The event focuses on the organic combination of social innovation and individual family creativity, and through children and families participating in various innovative educational activities, making innovation practice a cultural gene of the general public's families and making "hands-on" a new learning and living style for most families. It is reported that the "Love Home, Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival includes dozens of cutting-edge technology experience activities such as "Douguo Maker" experience activities, Laoniu Children's Exploration Museum anniversary celebration and "Exploration Family Loves Children's Day" activities, VR popular experience plan, and "Maker Tribe" interactive workshops.
